A chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Ekiti State, Senator Tony Adeniyi, has said Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu will win the party’s presidential primary. Adeniyi, who spoke in Akure while addressing members of the Tinubu Hope for Nigeria Vanguard, said some prominent Northerners began the push for Tinubu presidency. He said: “They urged us to begin the Southwest Agenda for Tinubu.”   Let peace reign, Sultan urges politicians     Terrorists use captives as human shield, says Buhari     Reschedule debts, get more loans, IMF tells Nigeria   Adeniyi said no aspirant could defeat Asiwaju Tinubu in Kano, Borno, Katsina, Sokoto, Kwara and other northern states. “Tinubu has the vision and passion to develop Nigeria. In politics it is not easy to stand and take a position. Asiwaju Tinubu has done a lot to prepare for this day. “Tinubu is already there. He has been going around. Nobody can defeat Asiwaju Tinubu in Kano, Borno, Katsina, Sokoto and Kwara. He will get 100 per cent of the votes from these places.”